Razorheart. Maybe your computer is not on, or your computer is not a Windows machine, but most likely your folder settings are set to not show system files.

The host file is part of windows (not adobe) so if it doesn't show up it's because your windows software is set to hide system files.

127.0.0.1 is the address of your computer. So, when those adobe links are called, they are redirected to the adress of your computer. In clear, the computer is calling itself instead of calling adobe.

An other way of preventing your computer from calling those adobe links is to instruct your firewall. So, you can simply put those links into the blocked zone. With this method, you don't need to alter your host file.

Regarding the updates, they will not be possible if they are done from one of those blocked adobe links. We need to know which link provides the updates.

"From Wingfoo:
If you are having trouble getting this to work, follow the instructions and install Photoshop, then download this torrent:

http://thepiratebay.org/torrent/6076932/Adobe_Photoshop_CS5_Extended_Activator_by_Carlos_Manuel_Virus_FR

There's a bunch of crap included in that torrent, but the file you are interested in is the one called "CS5 activation DLL.exe". Just ignore the other stuff. The exe is an archive that contains two files amtlib (2).dll and amtlib.dll.

The one called amtlib (2).dll is for 64bit Photoshop and the other one is for 32bit.
Go to the folder where Photoshop is installed and rename or delete the amtlib.dll file there, then just copy the correct file from the archive over (rename amtlib (2).dll to amtlib.dll if you're on 64bit).

This worked for me at least. "
